field.value:
In the ComponentRegistration class, there is a method overload for the
Properties() method with a description for the "filter" parameter which is
very hard to understand... :-) This is with Castle 3.0.0.4001 (using the
NuGet package).

{code}
        //
        // Summary:
        //     Filters properties on the implementation that will be considered 'settable'
        //     by the container.
        //
        // Parameters:
        //   filter:
        //     Predicate deciding whether a property is settable or not. If returns false
        //     container will ignore the property, otherwise property will be ignored.
        //
        // Remarks:
        //     Matched properties will be considered optional, that is component will resolve
        //     successfully if they can not be satisfied.
        public ComponentRegistration<TService> Properties(Predicate<PropertyInfo> filter); 
{code}
